description.1: STUFF OF LEGENDS PART 3 Spider-Man & Wolverine continue their globetrotting investigation.'
description.2: Spidey plays detective and tries to uncover the connection between Venom and his latest victims! Part 3 of the debut 5-issue story arc!
description.3: Witness the formation of the Archangels in the artificial Realm of Paradise ... and their plan to revolt against Mar-Vell and his new creation!
description.4: As the power-hungry Wilson Fisk conquers the violent gangs of Hell's Kitchen one crew at a time, a new battleground emerges in his quest for absolute power. But as the stakes are raised to new heights, the vigilante known as Spider-Man has Wilson Fisk in his crosshairs, and he's ready to end this young man's violent rise to power.
description.7: The four members of The Crew learn more about one another when James Rhodes reveals his secret identity as War Machine, and Josiah X reveals the Captain America suit he wears under his clothing...
description.9: The Punisher finds himself knee-deep in a gunrunning ring in the middle of Texas. He's getting to the bottom of the mystery, but will he make it out alive?
description.10: In a spell gone wrong, Spider-Man and Doctor Strange are tossed in and out of other dimensions!
description.11: As Home Base makes their move, the Hulk receives help from an unlikely place! Who is the mysterious Mr. Blue?
description.12: DROP DEAD GORGEOUS CONCLUSION Looks like Mystique has overstayed her welcome in Cuba. The shape shifter must make a difficult decision when trying to outrun sentinels hot in pursuit. But will innocent blood be spilt in her escape?
description.13: Fighting along side a squad of young'Jedi'whose'Masters'have been casualties of the'Clone Wars,'Anakin Skywalker'is finally feeling at peace with himself and the anger he holds inside. So, of course, he receives new orders to report to a rear echelon position, just as the "Padawan Pack" is commanded to hold an indefensible position against an overwhelming Separatist'attack!
description.14: The first story arc comes to a close, as the Torch confronts the Combustion Killer!
description.15: CULTURE SHOCK PART 2 Will the Inhumans find their footing or is the mission a no-go?
description.16: DEADPOOL WALKIN' PART 2 The Black Swan tries to explain the telepathic slip-up that connects him to Deadpool and Alex.
description.17: Sandy's family has gone bankrupt on a bogus oil drilling venture. But Namor has seen this coveted black liquid leaking out of the seabed before. Can the prince save Sandy's family? But at what cost?
description.18: The X-Men battle Azazel's horde, Lorna relives the massacre at Genosha and Northstar and Juggernaut have a frank discussion aboard the X-Jet on their way to see Squidboy.
description.20: Bruce Banner is on the run -- what else is new? But what are the secret motives of the mysterious Home Base?
description.21: PLANET X PART 1 The young mutant known as Dust runs rampant at the Xavier Institute as Xorn and his remedial class assist Professor X in his efforts to quell her.
description.23: The Punisher calls the gang out for a high noon showdown in retaliation for the attack on Sheriff Southall.
description.25: Max Anthony has been rescued, and the Black Panther has won the day! But this victory is followed by a bittersweet declaration - T'Challa has decided to become the Black Panther once more!
description.26: Dani's mutant recruitment leads her to Chicago, where she finds the child she is after has already made contact with another mutant - Dani's old teammate Karma!
description.27: Nightcrawler is in danger of being overrun by a horde of extradimensional beings. Plus, what decision has Squidboy made?
description.35: Bruce Banner does his best detective work, investigating a suicide that has been possibly framed.
description.36: Archangel is still reluctant to help Magik in the healing of a young mutant boy, but Ilyana won't take no for an answer! Meanwhile, the rest of the Exiles continue to battle Havok!
description.37: The Exiles and the X-Men - working together at last! But is the reconciliation between the teams too late to save Havok from himself?
description.38: With Mesmero's powers gone, he is sent to the Neverland Concentration Camp! Will Washout take out The Director before he is dealt the same hand?
description.41: Once they were just normal citizens - a police officer, a firefighter and an EMT worker - who risked their lives to help save others. Now, they are super humans united against Jeriah Halidon, an underground menace who has already threatened someone close to the Call!
description.42: Night indeed falls on Yancy Street in this conclusion of the 4-issue limited series. But only time will tell if the sun will again rise for Ben Grimm!
description.43: STUFF OF LEGENDS PART 2 Spider-Man and Wolverine's adventure takes them to Japan as they investigate an international mystery.
description.44: The fan favorite team of writer Paul Jenkins and artist Humberto Ramos reteam for an ongoing series starring the Amazing Spider-Man! And the series kicks off with a bang - enter Venom!
description.45: Spidey faces off against his deadliest foe, Venom!
description.47: Wilson Fisk's brutal rise from young gun to top dog is chronicled in this gritty ongoing crime drama - set in a not-so-friendly neighborhood.
description.50: Meet Danny Vincent - he's the nicest scoundrel you'll ever find! Just don't believe his lies!
description.51: Locked in deadly battle with Killmonger, the Black Panther is presented with an impossible choice. Can Kevin Cole truly trust information given to him by a man he has sworn to defeat?
description.52: Reed, ever the scientist, must force himself to learn and believe in magic in order to defeat Doom.
description.53: A mysterious villain is making a bid for power, and nobody is safe. When Spider-Girl's secret base of operations is destroyed, May Parker realizes the chilling truth: whoever is after her knows her secret identity!
description.54: After discovering the sick fetish of the X-Statix's head mortician, Dead Girl gets her own revenge- not once, but twice. You only die once, right?
description.56: "HIGHER LEARNING" pt. 2. A young Emma Frost continues to explore the ramifications of her blossoming powers...
description.57: SHIVER PART 4 Who is "Suit?" Will he be the one to take Venom down? Or will Robertson finally meet a gruesome end?
description.58: In an alien land, against an army of inhuman enemies, Wolverine's own humanity threatens to slip away as he's overcome by a berserker rage!
description.59: Kitty is captive in Mt. Haven, and only the X-Treme X-Men can save her! Plus, a grudge match between Wolverine and Lady Deathstrike culminates in a shocking conclusion!
description.60: Juston spends more and more time fixing the robot to the point where he can finally take him out for a test drive. Will this end in disaster, or be the moment Juston goes from drab to cool?
description.61: FINAL ISSUE! In Part 2 of the story starring Spider-Man, the choices Axum must make coincide with the presence of a figure familiar to the classic T-Bolts: Man-Killer, as well as the Scorpion.
description.66: Collects Wolverine: XISLE #1-5.  Intending to spend a rare carefree moment at a carnival with his beloved stepdaughter Amiko, Wolverine shows a violent side of himself that sends the young girl running in fear. Unable to face what he's done, Logan is propelled into a soul-searching adventure he may not be able to escape. What did he do? And what did young Amiko see?
description.69: Collects Startling Stories: Fantastic Four - Unstable Molecules #1-4.  In 1961 the first issue of THE FANTASTIC FOUR was drawn and written by the brilliant team of Jack Kirby and Stan Lee and set a new standard for heroic adventure comics. Few people realize that the Fantastic Four -- a family of sci-fi adventurers gifted with amazing powers -- were actually based on the lives of real people. As often is the case, real life was as astonishing as fiction. UNSTABLE MOLECULES is a biography that revisits the Fantastic Four's beginnings with a historian's eye.
description.70: The dominos start to fall uncontrollably as Marv's judicial actions bring forth violent reactions!
description.76: CULTURE SHOCK PART 1 Thanks to the fiery temper of Nahrees and the naivet' of Alaris, the Inhumans are flat broke and need to find a way to pay off their debt...quickly.
description.77: DROP DEAD GORGEOUS PART 5 While trying to infiltrate the Cuban Sentinel Program, Mystique finds herself in the midst of a mutant social-rights rebellion.
description.78: Peter and M.J. notice red lightening, and Peter jumps into action as Spider-Man! Spidey joins a battle with Iron Man, The Fantastic Four, Thor and Cyclops! All vs. the Mindless Ones!
description.79: Who is the Combustion Killer? And what pyro-powers does he have that Johnny Storm doesn't?
description.80: DEADPOOL WALKIN' PART 1 Agent X and Taskmaster get a chauffeuring job! Plus, a "hero" that was presumed dead returns!
description.81: Beautiful'Twi'lek'Jedi'Aayla Secura'goes undercover to ferret out a Separatist'enclave. But when her cover is blown, Aayla finds herself going up against famed'bounty hunter, and infamous'Jedi killer, Aurra Sing!
description.82: Liz and Sandy head down underneath he surface for Namorita's birthday. It's all fun and games until the authentic Atlantean cuisine is rolled out!
description.83: This is it: the final showdown with the Interrogator!
description.84: The final showdown between Hulk and the Absorbing Man!
description.86: Small-town sheriff Steve Southall, petitions the Punisher for assistance in protecting the town from the gang of gun-runners headed their way. As the Punisher puts his plan into action, the Sheriff heads out to intercept the gang before they reach the town.
description.87: Peter goes as Spider-Man to try and reconnect Melissa with her criminal brother Joshua.
description.88: Thanos is the only person who can save the universe. But will he?
description.90: Nightcrawler steals an X-Jet to get to Isla Des Demonas. Iceman's secondary mutation is revealed. And Juggernaut heads to Canada with Northstar in tow.
description.98: When'his master'is killed in a'battle'with'Jabiimi'rebels,'Anakin Skywalker finds himself assigned to a'squad'of similarly "orphaned"'Padawans. The non-stop rain and violent storms on'Jabiim'suit Anakin's mood of despair punctuated with rage. Some of the other Padawans feel the same way. Whether they're aware of it or not, they all have chips on their shoulders and are looking for either revengeor a way to follow their dead masters in death.

0.text: SPIRAL PART 8 With Asgard and New York destroyed there is but one final battle left. Oftentimes, a man's worst enemy is his own self. This is especially true for the gods. Now, Thor will battle Jake Olson, for the throne...

3.text: Witness the formation of the Archangels in the artificial Realm of Paradise ... and their plan to revolt against Mar-Vell and his new creation!

5.text: Vegas Bleeds Neon Part 2 (of 3).  The seedy underbelly of Las Vegas is even seedier than Iron Man thought.  After uncovering a UFO, what deadly secret may cost Tony his humanity?

6.text: It's a "How To" Issue as we take a look behind the curtain and witness how Elektra tries to assassinate a ruthless African dictator in the second part of this 3-part story arc!

19.text: The woman following Logan is not who she seems. Where do her loyalties lie and where does Logan fit into her plan?

21.text: PLANET X PART 1 The young mutant known as Dust runs rampant at the Xavier Institute as Xorn and his remedial class assist Professor X in his efforts to quell her.
PLANET X PART 1 The young mutant known as Dust runs rampant at the Xavier Institute as Xorn and his remedial class assist Professor X in his efforts to quell her.

22.text: The Runaways discover...a dinosaur!? What have their parents been keeping from the Runaways?!

24.text: While establishing the Rebel base on Yavin IV, General Dodonna clashes with fellow Rebel commander Roons Sewell over plans for the future of the still fledgling Alliance. Sewell is a charismatic leader who has won the hearts and minds of the rebel rank and file, but his flair for the dramatic worries the more pragmatic Dodonna. It's age and experience versus youth and vigor. But with the Empire searching for the new base, and ready to swoop in and destroy the rebels at the first opportunity, the behind the scenes struggle between Dodonna and Sewell could have unexpected, and unwanted, results for the Alliance!

28.text: Peter Parker's double life comes back to bite him when he winds up facing his latest foe -- detention! Luckily, the X-Men are on hand to intercede and Spider-Man gets an offer he can't refuse!

29.text: ASSAULT ON WEAPON + PART 4 Now in the Weapon + nerve center, in Earth orbit, the mutant trio attempt to take the whole operation down. Can they destroy Weapon XV? Plus, Wolverine finds his own Weapon + project files! What will he learn?

30.text: HOMELAND SECURITY PART 5 The Ultimates walk straight into a trap in Micronesia and are caught in a gargantuan atomic explosion. Have any of them survived?

31.text: BLOCKBUSTER PART 2 The Ultimates' Black Widow guest-stars as Spider-Man tries to work closely with Wolverine to discover who was behind the near-fatal attack on the X-Man last issue!

33.text: The Red Zone spreads, and the body count rises. With some weakened and others imprisoned, can even the Avengers endure?

34.text: HARDCORE PART 4 When Bullseye shows up to murder another one of Matt Murdock's girlfriends, Daredevil does something unexpected, something that lives up to the name of this story arc.

40.text: SPIRAL PART 7 Those who oppose Thor have conspired to remove him from Earth's affairs once and for all. Can Thor prove he is on the side of right or is he doomed to fail once again?

46.text: COMMUNION PART 1 Children all around the world are vanishing, spirited away by a gleaming figure from the stars! Are these just routine cases of alien abduction, or the harbinger of something far more sinister?

48.text: Vegas Bleeds Neon Part 1 (of 3).  After the events of Manhunt, Tony begins to rebuild his life.  On a trip to Vegas, he gets more than he bargained for as his armor turns flesh and blood and starts attacking him?!

49.text: Part 1 of a new 3-part story arc that takes Elektra around the globe to hunt down an elusive African dictator. You won’t wanna miss this!

55.text: Logan heads to another town on another lead. But someone has followed him out there. Can Logan get to the bottom of this murder case before the people responsible claim another innocent life?

57.text: SHIVER PART 4 Who is "Suit?" Will he be the one to take Venom down? Or will Robertson finally meet a gruesome end?

63.text: Before manga hit it big, Art Adams brought big monsters, big eyes and cute girls to the Marvel Universe. This volume collects the best of Adams' Marvel work, from his landmark work on the X-Men to his odd-couple new FF team of Spider-Man, the Hulk, Wolverine & Ghost Rider.

64.text: The secret organization hell-bent on capturing the Incredible Hulk has hired the services of one of his deadliest and oldest foes, The Abomination! Two of the Marvel Universe's most powerful adversaries go head-to-head and toe-to-toe in a gamma-powered slugfest!

65.text: The early adventures of Marvel's First Family continues, featuring showdowns with the Incredible Hulk, Namor, Dr. Doom and the shape-shifting Super-Skrull, who has all the combined powers of the FF! Plus Ant-Man, Spider-Man and the mysterious Watcher!

66.text: Intending to spend a rare carefree moment at a carnival with his beloved stepdaughter Amiko, Wolverine shows a violent side of himself that sends the young girl running in fear. Unable to face what he's done, Logan is propelled into a soul-searching adventure he may not be able to escape. What did he do? And what did young Amiko see?

68.text: More Ultimate Spider-Man team-ups written Brian Michael Bendis and drawn by the biggest names in comics including appearances by The Ultimates' Black Widow and Nick Fury, Shang Chi,  Master of Kung Fu and an all-star jam featuring Spidey and every hero in the Marvel Ultimate Universe!

69.text:
The Eisner Award-winning collection is in print! In 1961, the first issue of FANTASTIC FOUR was drawn and written by the brilliant team of Jack Kirby and Stan Lee, and set a new standard for heroic adventure comics. Few people realize that the Fantastic Four - a family of sci-fi adventurers gifted with amazing powers - was actually based on the lives of real people. As often is the case, real life was as astonishing as fiction. UNSTABLE MOLECULES is a biography that revisits the Fantastic Four's beginnings with a historian's eye.
Collects the critically acclaimed four-issue limited series!
128 PGS./EXPLICIT CONTENT ...$13.99

The best-selling graphic novel now available in softcover trade paperback format!

Investigating the murder of a teenage girl, Cage suddenly learns that a three-way gang war is under way for control of the turf he calls home. And what better way to disrupt the stalemate than offering his services to the highest bidder?

75.text:
The epic, visionary EARTH X saga continues! Will the heroes of Earth be able to solve the problems of the Paradise they helped create? Will their quest for a new Death entity succeed so the pain and suffering of the world's population ceases?
Collects HERALDS #1-3, PARADISE X #0-5 & XEN Special!

85.text: The start of a whole new Marvel Universe begins here! It's the Marvel Universe in the year 1602.

88.text: Thanos is the only person who can save the universe. But will he?

89.text: After discovering that their parents are super-villians, the Runaways make their escape to make sense of it all...but they end up making an evern more startling discovery.

91.text: When talking fails, it's web-shooters to the rescue!Â  Spider-Man finally has it out with one of his out of control classmates...until the X-Men come calling that is!

92.text: ASSAULT ON WEAPON + PART 3 Cyclops, Fantomex, and Wolverine must contend with The World's defenses-Car Cops! But even if they succeed, will they be able to take down the rogue Weapon XV?

93.text: BLOCKBUSTER PART 1 Why is Wolverine running from the X-Men? That's for Bendis to know and you to find out!

95.text:
More ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN team-ups written by BRIAN BENDIS and drawn by the biggest names in comics! Featuring appearances by THE ULTIMATES' Black Widow & Nick Fury, Shang Chi, and an all-star jam featuring Spidey and every hero in the MARVEL Ultimate Universe!
Collects ULTIMATE MARVEL TEAM-UP #14-16 & ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN SPECIAL!
Collects AMAZING FANTASY #15; AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #1-10.

96.text:
The story that inspired SUPREME POWER by J. Michael Straczynski & Gary Frank!
Before WATCHMEN, before KINGDOM COME, before THE AUTHORITY, there was SQUADRON SUPREME, a deconstructionist view of the super-hero paradigm in a real world setting. Published before such stories became commonplace, it set the standard for post-modernist super-hero fiction, and influenced a generation of creators.
Collects ASM (Vol. 1) #11-19, ANNUAL #1

97.text:
Master of the Mystic Arts, a sorcerer supreme, a white knight who wields black magic against blacker villains. Doctor Strange is mankind's only hope against the dark otherworldly forces that conspire to steal the life of the conscious world - forces such as Baron Mordo, the Dread Dormammu, Nightmare, Aggamon, The House of Shadows, Loki, the Mindless Ones, and more.
Collects STRANGE TALES #110-111, 114-141
